Durban - Pietermaritzburg police are searching for an 11-year-old pupil who was last seen on November 9. Andile Fihla, 11, was in the company of his sister and both were headed to Msilinga Primary School in Copesville at around 7:30 am, police said. "While walking, a man who is known to them as well as his friend residing in the area stopped to talk to Andile. "They instructed his sister to continue walking to school and that Andile will follow soon. A member of the community noticed what was going on and informed Andile’s mother. She contacted the school only to find out that Andile did not arrive at school. The matter was reported to police for investigation. Police searched for Andile but he was nowhere to be found." Police are appealing to anyone with information to contact the investigating officer, Constable SC Makhaya on 079 500 1330 or 033 387 9600 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111. Daily News